          <code code="11506-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Progress Notes" />
          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/22/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Post-hip fracture follow-up, dementia management.
HPI: 78yo female, 2 months s/p right hip ORIF after mechanical fall at home. PT 3x/week, progressing well. Now walking with rolling walker. Pain controlled with scheduled acetaminophen. Daughter reports increased confusion at night (sundowning). MMSE today 18/30 (was 20/30 in Sept). Donepezil + memantine continued.
PE: Surgical site well-healed. ROM right hip 0-100 degrees flexion. Gait -- slow, steady with walker. No TTP spine. Oriented x2 (person, place). Clock draw: 2/5.
Assessment:
# Alzheimer dementia (G30.1): Progressive decline. MMSE 18. Continue donepezil/memantine. Caregiver education on sundowning -- consistent routine, night light, no caffeine after noon.
# s/p Hip fracture (Z96.641): Healing well. Continue PT. Fall prevention: remove throw rugs, grab bars installed.
# Osteoporosis (M80.08): Started alendronate + calcium/D post-fracture. Vit D level now 35 (was 22).
# HTN (I10): BP 126/72. Metoprolol appropriate -- not over-treating.
# Depression (F33.1): Daughter reports less tearfulness on sertraline. PHQ-9 difficult to administer (cognitive limitations).
Plan: Continue all meds. PT continue 6 more weeks. Home safety re-evaluation. Consider adult day program for socialization. Caregiver support group info given. Return 6 weeks. Advance directive review with daughter.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>01/15/2026</td><td>Gretchen Lockard, MD</td><td>Acute Visit</td><td>CC: Fall at home, right hip pain, unable to bear weight.
HPI: 78yo with dementia found on floor by daughter at 6 AM. Uncertain how long she was down. Complains of right hip pain. Unable to stand.
PE: Right leg shortened and externally rotated. TTP right groin. Neurovascular intact distally.
XR: Right femoral neck fracture, displaced.
Assessment: Right hip fracture (S72.001A). Osteoporosis likely contributing.
Plan: Orthopedic consult -- ORIF performed 01/20/2026. Post-op course uncomplicated. Discharged to SNF for rehab 01/25/2026. Start osteoporosis treatment after surgical healing (6 weeks). DEXA ordered. PT/OT daily at SNF.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
